{"article_id":"8UgbC6IE1TtvJat3","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"House Republicans gave ground Thursday in the debt ceiling fight","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"by offering to raise the nation ' s borrowing limit for six weeks ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"and the White House said","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"President Obama might sign such a measure","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"to avoid default .","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"With the barest outlines of a deal on the table ,","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"as the partial government shutdown entered its 10th day ,","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"Mr. Obama met for more than an hour late Thursday with Speaker John A. Boehner and other GOP leaders at the White House ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"before the Republicans leaders scurried back to the Capitol","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"to huddle .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"\" The takeaway from the meeting was our teams are going to be talking further , \"","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"said House Majority Leader Eric Cantor , Virginia Republican .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"The White House said","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"the meeting was worthwhile","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"but insisted","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"\" no specific determination was made . \"","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"The Republicans proposed a six-week limit increase to the $ 16.7 trillion debt ceiling in exchange for the White House agreeing to talk about a broad set of fiscal issues .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"But Senate Democrats remain a sticking point .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"Majority Leader Harry Reid said","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"he ' s not sure what to expect out of the House GOP .","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"\" We ' ll just wait","depth":13},{"id":21,"text":"and see ,","depth":13},{"id":22,"text":"because they can not decide what they want , \"","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"And late in the evening he set up a key filibuster test vote for Saturday on his preferred option ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"which would impose a 15-month debt holiday ,","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"allowing Mr. Obama to borrow freely until after the 2014 congressional elections .","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"The mere suggestion of a debt deal by Mr. Boehner sent the stock markets soaring on Thursday ,","depth":5},{"id":28,"text":"showing how keenly business leaders are watching the negotiations .","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"The administration says","depth":5},{"id":30,"text":"the government will run out of room","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"to borrow more money on Oct. 17","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"and will have to resort to paying out of cash on hand .","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"That would probably mean missing payments to Social Security recipients and veterans ,","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"Treasury Secretary Jacob Lew told Congress on Thursday ,","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"laying out consequences","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"if the debt limit is fully reached .","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"He pointedly did not mention halting payments on the debt ,","depth":5},{"id":38,"text":"but said","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"he shouldn ' t be forced to pick and choose between other programs .","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"Still , he declined to say exactly how he would prioritize ,","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"leaving vague the exact consequences .","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"\" I think","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"prioritization is just default by another name , \"","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"The debt negotiations have overshadowed the shutdown ,","depth":4},{"id":46,"text":"which began Oct. 1","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"when Congress and Mr. Obama were unable to agree on how to fund the government in fiscal year 2014 .","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"Continuing to deal with the shutdown fallout ,","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"the House passed a bill","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"to restore more Border Patrol operations ,","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"adding to its list of piecemeal bills .","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"The Senate , meanwhile , tolled its 10th day","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"without holding a floor vote on any of those proposals .","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"The chamber did , however , clear a bill","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"to ensure","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"families of troops","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"killed in action","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"will be able to immediately receive the $ 100,000 death benefit","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"they are due .","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"The White House said","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"that was unnecessary","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"since it had found a work-around","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"that had a private foundation pay the benefits , with a promise","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"that it will be reimbursed","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"after the shutdown ends .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"Still , Mr. Obama will have to decide whether to sign the new bill .","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"The Obama administration also signaled","depth":6},{"id":68,"text":"it is willing to relent on some of its closures of national parks ,","depth":6},{"id":69,"text":"telling the Associated Press","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"it would seek to allow states to use their own money","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"to fund operations at some sites .","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"It remained unclear late Thursday","depth":4},{"id":73,"text":"whether the GOP was still focused solely on a debt deal","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"or whether it would accept adding a shutdown deal into the mix .","depth":5},{"id":75,"text":"House Republicans ' debt proposal was vague","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"when Mr. Boehner laid it out for reporters Thursday morning ,","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"after conferring with the House Republican Conference .","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"\" I don ' t want to put anything on the table ,","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"I don ' t want to take anything off the table , \"","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"The White House reacted cooly","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"but didn ' t rule out","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"that Mr. Obama might go along with the GOP proposal .","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"\" The president is happy","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"that cooler heads at least seem to be prevailing in the House , \"","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"said White House press secretary Jay Carney ,","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"who added","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"that the GOP proposal \" seems to be a recognition","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"that default is not an option . \"","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"\" It is certainly at least an encouraging sign ...","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"that they ' re not listening to the debt-limit and default deniers , \"","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"But Mr. Carney also said","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"the president \" strongly prefers \" a Senate bill","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"that would raise the borrowing limit beyond the 2014 elections .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"\" We ' ll see what they ' re able to pass ,","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"and consider it then , \"","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"he said of House Republicans ' proposal .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":197,"left":143,"right":196,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":127,"right":142,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":103,"right":126,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":100,"right":102,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":101,"right":4,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":126,"left":124,"right":125,"relation"